 St. Valentine’s day Movie night concept. Movie night message on board, laptop, popcorn, red candle, gift, hearts decor, two cups of cocoa with marshmallows for a couple. Cozy holiday plans for lovers Valentine is coming where is your boyfriend. The one day a year set out for lovers, Valentine’s Day is bound to have everywhere packed and filled with people finding the perfect way to spend time with their partners. If this isn’t you or you want a more personal experience while not spend lovers day binge watching Nollywood’s biggest love films on Netflix. Need some film ideas? Here are our favourite Nollywood films to binge watch this Valentine. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1318329 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-974x548.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-Weeks-In-Lagos-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Are you a fan of a rom-com involving a clash between two social classes? This film is perfect for you. The plot kicks off with the return of a businessman Nigeria who falls in love with a friend’s sister despite his family’s plan for him to marry a politician’s daughter. Set in Lagos and London, the movie tells the story of a passionate London chef, ‘Ope’, who was trying to follow her dream of opening a restaurant in London, but was frustrated by her lack of progress. The memory of Zainab Balogun descending the stairs in a beautiful red gown still lingers in our heads. Earning a TIFF 2017 selection, this film revolves around a disenchanted chef tries to help her parents restore their falling hotel but cooks up feelings for an investor with his sights set on the property. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1399434 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="721" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-640x361.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-974x549.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Dear-Affy-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Released in 2020, this film tells the story of an engaged couple who hit a number of speed bumps on their road to matrimony including major career complications and questions of fidelity. Tango with me Photo Iroko Tv In this film, Geneive Nnaji and Joseph Benjamin play a newly married couple that journeys through self-discovery and healing while dealing with the aftermath of a traumatic event on their wedding night. Kasanova Photo Imdb Don’t we all love rom-coms with the saviour trope. After losing his wife, a single father indulges in flimsy flings until he meets his son’s music teacher, who imparts a few lessons on love. Special Jollof Photo Imdb Blending African and American culture, this moves centers around a journalist who goes undercover at a Nigerian restaurant to expose undocumented immigrants –until love strikes. The Bridge Photo Imdb Tribal prejudice is a major theme explored in this film. A Yoruba prince and a young lady from a prominent Igbo family face tribal prejudice and parental pressure when they secretly wed. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1349871 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-974x548.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Namaste-Wahala-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> What happens when Nollywood meets Bollywood? An interracial romance hits humorous and heart-wrenching hiccups as the couple’s parents fight tooth and nail against their relationship. Flower girl. Photo- Imdb Damilola Adegbite delivers an amazing performance in this film. When a young florist who’s long dreamed of her wedding day gets dumped by her boyfriend, she sets out to win him back with help from a handsome actor. Kambili Photo Imdb Everyone wants to get hitched but a lady called Kambili is determined to marry before she turns 30. This makes her change her impulsive ways and do whatever it takes to win back the boyfriend who left her. Small chops. Photo- Imdb Contrary to its title, it’s not about food. When a business mogul hires an exotic dancer for a weekend of entertainment, it quickly morphs into a messy situation full of misunderstanding. Fine wine Photo Imdb Starring Richard Mofe Damijo and Zainab Balogun, the film explores the age gap issue in a romantic relationship. After falling for a woman much younger than him, a wealthy man must confront the social stigma around age gap romances. She is. Photo-Imdb Released in 2019, this film shows a successful and single woman under pressure from her family and friends to settle down, she searches for the right partner, refusing to settle for less. Love is war. Photo-Imdb Directed by the talented Omoni Oboli, an adoring couple test the strength of their marriage when they run against each other for the office of the state governor. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1666431 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-423x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1810" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-423x598.jpg 423w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-815x1152.jpg 815w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-1086x1536.jpg 1086w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-1448x2048.jpg 1448w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-170x240.jpg 170w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-339x480.jpg 339w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-424x600.jpg 424w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/The-eve.-Photo-Imdb-scaled.jpg 1810w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Another film with Beverley Naya stellar performance. At an epic beach party thrown by his buddies, a groom-to-be meets a lovely stranger who makes him rethink the meaning of life and true love. When Love Happens Photo Imdb From the creative direction of Seyi Babatope comes an amazing 2016 film. Fed up with coordinating weddings for everyone else, unlucky-in-love event planner Mo turns to the internet to see if she can find her own Mr. Right Ayamma Photo The Nigerian Voice A one-of-a-kind magical fusion cultural film, an engaged prince dreams of a beautiful, singing maiden and is then shocked to come across a woman who looks and sounds exactly like her. It’s her Day Photo Nollywood Reinvented Laugh your heart out this valentine. After a man promises his fiancé a dream wedding, he must keep up with her outrageous requests to have the most lavish ceremony possible. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-508872 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-479x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1598" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-479x598.jpg 479w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-446x557.jpg 446w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-192x240.jpg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-384x480.jpg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2-481x600.jpg 481w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/The-Wedding-Party-2.jpg 865w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Often regarded as the film that predicted the union of Banky W and Adesua Ewatomi. As their big day arrives, a couple’s lavish wedding plans turn into a nightmare of exes, fighting parents, and uninvited guests. Think of this as our valentine’s gift to you. Hope you enjoyed reading this article? Remember to share your favorite movies off our list with your friends.